.SH NAME
bnx2x_func_chk_transition \- perform function state machine transition
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" bnx2x_func_chk_transition
.BI "(struct bnx2x *bp "  ","
.BI "struct bnx2x_func_sp_obj *o "  ","
.BI "struct bnx2x_func_state_params *params "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bp" 12
device handle
.IP "o" 12
function info
.IP "params" 12
state parameters
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
It both checks if the requested command is legal in a current
state and, if it's legal, sets a `next_state' in the object
that will be used in the completion flow to set the `state'
of the object.

returns 0 if a requested command is a legal transition,
-EINVAL otherwise.
